# Mandatory project standards

## Vala code

Before writing or changing **any** Vala code:

1. Read **`docs/coding-standards-router.md`** in full (**top mistake: don't add helper methods** — inline unless user/plan names them).
2. Follow **`.cursor/rules/vala-coding-standards-router.mdc`** (same checklist;
   applies when `*.vala` files are in context).
3. Read **only** the `docs/coding-standards.md` sections the router maps you to
   (grep `section: <slug>`; read each block in full).
4. Before finishing: read section `agent-compliance-gate` and run its checks.

Do **not** read all of `docs/coding-standards.md` unless your slug set includes
every section. Do **not** grep-or-skim sections instead of reading them whole.
Do **not** implement until router-mandated reads are done.

## Other full documents (read entire file when task applies)

| Task | Document |
|------|----------|
| Meson / build | `docs/build-rules.md` |
| Docblocks (when router includes `docblocks`) | `docs/code-documentation.md` |
| Plans in `docs/plans/*` | `docs/guide-to-writing-plans.md` |
| Bug fixes | `docs/bug-fix-process.md` |

Partial compliance is a violation.
